The National Assembly has jerked up the 2018 budget to N9.120 trillion from N8.612 trillion. The details of the budget were listed on the Order Paper obtained by our Correspondent. A breakdown of the budget which is to be laid before both chambers today ( Tuesday, May 15) shows that the sum of N530,421,368,624 is for statutory transfer; N2,203,835,365,699 is for debt service; N199 billion is for sinking fund for maturing loans; N3,516,477,902,077 is for recurrent (non debt) expenditure, while N2,869,600,351,825 is for development fund for capital expenditure. Details laterâ€¦